column295: "dc.description": "PURPOSE: A method for providing information and a gaze-actuated information system is provided to provide a pilot with information associated with at least one region of a field of view visible to the pilot from within a cockpit without requiring a visual display. CONSTITUTION: A method for providing information includes the steps of determining an eye gaze direction relative to a given frame of reference for at least one eye of a pilot(72); determining a reference direction relative to the given frame of reference(74); comparing the eye gaze direction with the reference direction(76); and generating audio output audible to the pilot and indicative of information associated with the reference direction
column296: if the eye gaze direction and the reference direction are equal to within a given degree of accuracy(78). Therefore
column297: automatic tracking and conforming of objects is performed without requiring a visual display."

column322: "dc.description": "The present invention relates to a movie film projection system capable of format conversion. More specifically
column323: another projection is based on the detection of a trigger strip encoded on a film that delivers a predetermined number of feed holes arranged per frame at a specified projection frame rate
column324: and then conveys the format characteristics of the incoming film. A film projector feeder capable of automatically switching to a different film format with a frame rate and a different number of feed holes per frame. The controller allows the system to automatically switch between different film formats and frame rates on the same projector and on the same disc of the film without substantial interruption or delay in projector operation."

column356: "dc.description": "A method for distributing documents to multiple receiving stations associated with multiple users via a communication network is disclosed. At least one document layout is pointcast to each receiving station
column357: the document layout associated with a given user and defining one or more data objects such as text
column358: images and graphics. Collections of shared data objects are then multicast to the receiving stations based on respective user document layouts via the communication network.
